data.chText: 打开（箱、包等）取；从（箱、包等中）取出
data.enText: to take things out of a suitcase, bag, etc.

data.chText: 我一到达就打开行李，整理衣物。
data.enText: I unpacked my bags as soon as I arrived.

data.chText: 她取出所有要穿的衣服，其余的都留在箱子里。
data.enText: She unpacked all the clothes she needed and left the rest in the case.

data.chText: 她回到自己的卧室打开行李取出衣物。
data.enText: She went to her room to unpack.
to separate sth into parts so that it is easier to understand

simple_means.memory_skill: un 打开，解开，弄出 + pack 包裹 → 打开包裹（或行李等）

value.def: When you unpack a suitcase, box, or similar container, or you unpack the things inside it, you take the things out of the container.

example.ex: Our guide unpacked a picnic of ham sandwiches and offered us tea.
example.tran: 我们的导游打开装着火腿三明治的野餐盒，并给我们倒了些茶水。

value.tran: 打开（箱、盒等）；（从箱、盒等中）取出

value.def: If you unpack an idea or problem, you analyse it and consider it in detail.

example.ex: A lot of ground has been covered in unpacking the issues central to achieving this market-led strategic change.
example.tran: 在分析实现这个以市场为导向的战略转变的关键问题时，涉及了诸多领域。
